# 0:00 TAUGHT TO BE FRIENDS OF PEACE (3 min.)

A marvelous prophecy of peace is being fulfilled today 
-  **Isaiah 2:2-4** KSI vs 2 and 3
![04-01 mountain.jpeg](data:image/png;base64,)
Those who are taught by Jehovah do not fight in the wars of the nations 
 - **is 54:13** KSI
- But is the prophecy found at Isaiah 2:2-4 only about neutrality? No
	- We enjoy a peaceful, worldwide unity that has no social, racial, or national divisions
	- We must do our part to maintain that peaceful unity

- Going to review 3 areas: 
   - entertainment
   - preaching
   - congregation

# 0:03 1. REJECT VIOLENT ENTERTAINMENT (8 min.)

- Much of the world’s entertainment is violent and thus, in effect, teaches war; such entertainment can influence our thinking and actions (
	- **Pr 22:24, 25** - Not get involved with one disposed to rage....so that you never learn his ways
	- World infatuated with violence (music, video games, movies, websires......news)
	- Watch news violence....watch movies violence.....games....happen person fight? peace? no
	- watch peace.....happen person fight? peace will

- We must learn to hate violence as Jehovah does 
- **Read Psalm 11:5** KSL - jah hates anyone loving violence

	- Because of his hatred for those who love violence, Jehovah destroyed an entire world 
            "I have decided c go put an end to all flesh because the earth is full of violence"
        ![04-02 violence.jpg](data:image/png;base64,)
- Our choice of entertainment may indicate what is happening in our heart (Lu 6:45 if time)
	- If we are attracted to violent entertainment, we should beg Jehovah to help us to stop being entertained by what he hates
	- Speak to a mature Christian about the matter; ask for suggestions and for help to monitor your progress

- Let Jehovah help you cultivate peace, goodness, and self-control


# 0:11 2. BE A FRIEND OF PEACE WHEN PREACHING (8 min.)

- Some people get angry when we share the message of peace with them
	- Some are opposed to the truth, others may be distressed by personal problems or family tragedy, or we may have called at a bad time
	![04-03 preach.jpeg](data:image/png;base64,)
- Jesus set the pattern when seeking friends of peace 
	- He did not engage in noisy arguments, and he was peaceable even when under pressure 
	- People responded favorably to Jesus’ teachings because of his mild and gracious speech 

- Our demeanor in the ministry should match our peaceful message
- This message urges people to seek a peaceful relationship with Jehovah 
	- To find a friend of peace, we must be peaceable 
	- **Read 2 Timothy 2:24** KSL- slave of the lord not need to fight...gentle, retraint

- If a person responds angrily, we should reply mildly and graciously 
	- if time  **Pr 17:27** - discerning man remain calm
	- We cannot control a person’s response to our message, but we can control our own reaction 
	- **Pr 12:20** - those counseling peace have rejoicing

- We will have the privilege to teach the ways of peace to millions of resurrected people with varying backgrounds, temperaments, and personalities
	- The training we receive now as peacemakers will benefit us in the new world

# 0:19 3. PROMOTE PEACE IN THE CONGREGATION (8 min.)

- Wisdom from above motivates us to be peaceable
- **Read James 3:17, 18** KSL
	- Even if a brother has habits or traits that annoy us, we should pursue peace
	- The way we treat fellow worshippers has a direct bearing on relationship with jah 
![04-04 peace.jpg](data:image/png;base64,)
- When offended, a friend of peace can choose to overlook the offense (Pr 10:12)

- If the offense cannot be overlooked, take steps to restore peace 
- Think in advance about what to say and how to say it in a peaceful way (abraham and lsot sif time **Ge 13:8, 9** KSL
- ![04-06 abraham lot.jpeg](data:image/png;base64,)
	
	- Earnestly seek Jehovah’s help in prayer 
	- If the initial discussion does not produce the results you desire, look for another opportunity to make peace 

- Our pursuing peaceful relations with our brothers will result in happiness (result sons of god if time **Mt 5:9)** KSL

# 0:27 PROVE YOURSELF A FRIEND OF PEACE (2 min.)

- We are instructed by the “God of peace” 
	- May we continue to prove ourselves friends of peace as we contribute to the fulfillment of the prophecy at Isaiah 2:2-4

**Review question:** **How can we prove that we are friends of peace?**

**Answer: 
Psalm 11:5; jah hates loving violence - entertainment
2 Timothy 2:24; save of lord gentle - ministry
James 3:17, 18; friends of peace learn war no more; thus, we reject violent entertainment, we speak peaceably in the ministry, and we promote peace in the congregation**

As we unitedly pursue peace, we prove that the promise of an earth filled with peace-loving people is not just a dream; it will be a reality
